Marketing pricing FAQ

We do offer a free tier. You can create an account, import and sync your data, customize templates and emails, and use many of Klaviyos features for free. You can send 500 emails maximum to up to 250 contacts. You also get 150 mobile credits. Youll be prompted to upgrade once you exceed that limit.

Yes, absolutely. While many tools can send emails, SMS, or WhatsApp, Klaviyo stands out as the B2C CRM that helps you build deeper connections with your customers and drive lifetime value. We integrate all the data your customers generate, use AI and intuitive no-code tools to deliver the right message, at the right time, on the right channelacross every stage of the customer journey.

Carrier fees are additional charges applied by mobile carriers (like Verizon or Vodafone) to a business’s text messages. While many SMS providers exclude these fees, Klaviyo includes them in the upfront price, making it easier for businesses to understand the true cost per message without hidden surprises.

No, only outbound text messages and outbound marketing or transactional WhatsApp messages to customers cost credits.

Meta has temporarily paused the delivery of all marketing template messages to WhatsApp users with US phone numbers. However, utility and service template messagessuch as order updates and customer supportare still permitted. Were actively monitoring Metas policy updates and will keep you informed if and when marketing message delivery resumes in the US.

WhatsApp supports various message types Marketing, Utility (transactional), and Service each with distinct pricing determined by Meta and varying by recipient country. Our pricing is designed to reflect Metas underlying cost structure where we charge on a per-message basis, when a template message is delivered.

Additionally, all non-template messages are free. These can only be sent within a 24-hour customer service window that opens whenever a WhatsApp user messages you or calls you.

As your active profile count grows you will automatically move to a profile compliant plan. We recommend following Klaviyo’s guidance on which profiles to suppress, so that you aren’t paying for profiles that are no longer providing value.

Don’t worry. If you need more messages than your plan allows for you have the option to upgrade your plan. You can upgrade manually or select the option to automatically upgrade to the next plan as your sending volume grows. You can upgrade email and mobile channels independently.

We offer a variety of support to help you get started. Depending on your plan, you may have access to:

Step-by-step onboarding to our products and features
The Klaviyo Community where you can ask questions and learn from other Klaviyo customers
Klaviyo Academy for courses and certifications
Email and chat support with product experts
Growth success team for strategic questions
Agency partners to help with onboarding, strategy, and implementation

We accept all major credit cards and you can enter or update your payment details on your account page at any time.

You can manage your account from your account page.

A short code is a 5-6 digit phone number that businesses use to deliver text messages to their customers. Short codes have a higher throughput than toll-free numbers, so if your business needs to send SMS messages to more than 30,000 people at a time or relies heavily on MMS, we recommend upgrading from a complimentary toll-free number to a short code. Once you reach the recommended sending volume, Klaviyo will reach out to help you secure a dedicated short code for your business.

If you want a short code before reaching 30,000 people, you can request a short code and begin using it as soon as the application is approved by mobile carriers. The short code will come at an additional cost. Some brands choose to start sending from a short code immediately to prevent having to change the number that customers receive their texts from when migrating from a toll-free number to a short code.

A profile refers to an individual contact stored in your Klaviyo account, along with all of that contacts customer data: events, preferences, profile properties, and more. You can think of each profile as a digital file on a specific contact. Profiles can be one of two statuses active or suppressed.

Active profiles are any profiles that are able to be emailed by Klaviyo. Your number of active profiles is a factor in the Klaviyo plan you choose.

Suppressed profiles are profiles that cannot be emailed but still store all the relevant customer data. Suppressed profiles are not a factor in Klaviyo’s pricing.

Total profiles
The overall profile count is the total number of profiles associated with your Klaviyo account, regardless of their marketing status and channel (this includes Email, SMS, WhatsApp, and Push profiles today). Any profile that is being stored and tracked in Klaviyo will be represented in this count.

All of our base plans come with email, and you can choose to add mobile messaging to your plan, which includes both SMS and WhatsApp. You may increase email or mobile independently.

You can find more information about our pricing in the Help Center.

Service pricing FAQ

Klaviyo Service includes three products Customer Hub, Customer Agent, and Helpdesk. Pick the setup that works best for your business, and unlock even more value when you use them together.

Each product is designed to work independently, but they integrate seamlessly for a more powerful experience. You can start with one and add others anytime.

Yes. We offer a free 30-day trial for Customer Hub and Helpdesk, plus a one-time free trial of 50 conversations for Customer Agent. Start your free trials here.

Yes, early adopters can lock in a special introductory price list. Customers lock in on the introductory price list for as long as they maintain a subscription to the applicable product. If they cancel or end their subscription and later choose to re-purchase, theyll be subject to the then-current list price at the time of purchase.

Our special introductory pricing is available until December 31, 2025.

We do not charge hidden fees. Some plans include onboarding support for larger implementations, we offer optional paid services.

We will notify you in advance and provide easy options to upgrade. There are no surprise overage fees.

We offer a variety of support to help you get started. Depending on your plan, you may have access to:

  • Step-by-step onboarding to our products and features
  • The Klaviyo Community where you can ask questions and learn from other Klaviyo customers
  • Klaviyo Academy for courses and certifications
  • Email and chat support with product experts
  • Growth success team for strategic questions
  • Agency partners to help with onboarding, strategy, and implementation
